re influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Sandbach was born about 1362, in Hankelow, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Richard Sandbach. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Richard DeHassal."},"et":{"Abt 1362–Deceased":"umbes 1362–Surnud","1362–Female":"1362–Surnud","1358–Male":"1358–Surnud","1384–1467":"1384–1467","1386–Female":"1386–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","Abt 1362":"umbes 1362","1358":"1358","1467":"1467","1386":"1386","1384":"1384","1362":"1362","Hankelow, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hankelow, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1362–Deceased":"noin 1362–Kuollut","1362–Female":"1362–Kuollut","1358–Male":"1358–Kuollut","1384–1467":"1384–1467","1386–Female":"1386–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","Abt 1362":"noin 1362","1358":"1358","1467":"1467","1386":"1386","1384":"1384","1362":"1362","Hankelow, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hankelow, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1362–Deceased":"environ 1362–Décédée","1362–Female":"1362–Décédée","1358–Male":"1358–Décédé","1384–1467":"1384–1467","1386–Female":"1386–Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","Abt 1362":"environ 1362","1358":"1358","1467":"1467","1386":"1386","1384":"1384","1362":"1362","Hankelow, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hankelow, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Sandbach est née environ 1362, à Hankelow, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fille de Ri